The library Wserver allows to create an elementary Web service
receiving requests from Web browsers and answering them some html
code.

No http daemon running in your machine is required to make it work. It
is even not necessary to be connected to internet.

Written in ocaml, using the library unix.cma. The code is very small.

Available by ftp:
	ftp://ftp.inria.fr/lang/chamau/
Files:
	README.wserver
	wserver.tar.gz

